511
00:42:41,186 --> 00:42:43,981
This is Dr. Ramml,
one of our leading architects...

512
00:42:44,106 --> 00:42:47,609
and Dr. Brunner
from the Institute of Civil Engineering.

513
00:42:47,693 --> 00:42:49,736
Together,
we are the first bid.

514
00:42:49,862 --> 00:42:52,906
Bid, right.

515
00:42:53,031 --> 00:42:55,450
For what precisely?

516
00:43:04,877 --> 00:43:07,337
I love it.

517
00:43:07,421 --> 00:43:09,381
Good choice.

518
00:43:09,506 --> 00:43:13,385
Modern, elegant-
a symbol of Uganda's future.

519
00:43:13,468 --> 00:43:17,973
<i>- Here is where we will have the
next Pan-African Congress. - Nice.</i>

520
00:43:18,056 --> 00:43:22,019
My two closest advisors-

521
00:43:22,102 --> 00:43:25,022
Tweedledum and Tweedledee.

522
00:43:26,982 --> 00:43:30,527
- Look what Nicholas has designed for me.
- Nice.

523
00:43:30,611 --> 00:43:33,155
- I didn't design anything. It was more-
- That's nonsense.

524
00:43:33,238 --> 00:43:35,908
You have a wonderful eye.

525
00:43:36,033 --> 00:43:38,702
Jonah- he has...
no taste.

526
00:43:38,827 --> 00:43:41,288
<i>Look at him.</i>

527
00:43:41,413 --> 00:43:44,249
Even his suits,
they look silly.

528
00:43:44,374 --> 00:43:47,628
Is that not right, Jonah?

529
00:43:55,761 --> 00:43:57,721
What is it you want, Jonah?

530
00:43:57,804 --> 00:44:00,557
I have some ministerial papers
for your signature.

531
00:44:00,641 --> 00:44:02,809
Go.

532
00:44:02,935 --> 00:44:06,188
I will sign them later.

533
00:44:14,112 --> 00:44:16,573
I do not like the way
that man looks at me.

534
00:44:18,325 --> 00:44:20,786
Do you think
he looks at me strangely?

535
00:44:20,869 --> 00:44:23,580
No. No, I can't say
that I've noticed.

536
00:44:25,165 --> 00:44:27,417
Okay. Enlargement
of the medial sternum...

537
00:44:27,543 --> 00:44:30,379
and reticular nodular
lung patterns-

538
00:44:30,462 --> 00:44:32,214
<i>all indicating
pulmonary T.B.</i>

539
00:44:32,297 --> 00:44:35,342
Yeah, but it could be disseminated-

540
00:44:36,760 --> 00:44:40,013
What was that?

541
00:44:56,780 --> 00:45:00,450
Makindye Prison-
where Obote's people are being held.

542
00:45:00,576 --> 00:45:03,787
Can you hear that?

543
00:45:05,873 --> 00:45:08,333
<i>Dr. Garrigan! Dr. Garrigan!</i>

544
00:45:08,458 --> 00:45:10,419
Please! Come quickly.

545
00:45:10,502 --> 00:45:13,463
<i>The president's son
is sick.</i>

546
00:45:13,547 --> 00:45:16,425
What's wrong with him? What's wrong with him?

547
00:45:22,389 --> 00:45:26,894
<i>Can you hear me, child?
I'm begging you to stop it. Mackenzie!</i>

548
00:45:27,019 --> 00:45:29,271
- Thank you. You can step away.
- Stop it, Mackenzie. Please.

549
00:45:29,354 --> 00:45:33,400
- Thank you. Your son's epileptic?
- I don't know.

550
00:45:33,525 --> 00:45:35,777
- What? Has he been like this before?
- Yes.

551
00:45:35,861 --> 00:45:38,655
Right. Can you hold his knees
up against his chest?

552
00:45:38,739 --> 00:45:41,408
- Yeah, yeah.
- If you can do that. Okay. The other hand back here.

553
00:45:41,533 --> 00:45:43,994
<i>- This is Campbell?
- It's Mackenzie, Campbell's brother.</i>

554
00:45:44,119 --> 00:45:46,538
- Mackenzie? Right.
- Come on, Mackenzie. Come on, baby.

555
00:45:46,622 --> 00:45:49,833
Mackenzie,
I am Dr. Garrigan. Okay?

556
00:45:49,917 --> 00:45:51,960
<i>We're gonna
sort you out.</i>

557
00:45:52,044 --> 00:45:54,046
- We'll get you to hospital. It's gonna be fine.
- No, no, no.

558
00:45:54,129 --> 00:45:56,215
- The president will not allow it.
- I really think the child-

559
00:45:56,340 --> 00:45:59,009
- You must do what you can do from here.
- The child has to go to hospital.

560
00:45:59,092 --> 00:46:01,970
Please! Please.

561
00:46:04,598 --> 00:46:06,642
It's okay now, baby.
Mama's here.

562
00:46:06,725 --> 00:46:11,021
Mama is here.
It's okay. Mama's here.

563
00:46:11,146 --> 00:46:13,941
Okay. Okay.

564
00:46:14,066 --> 00:46:16,902
<i>There you are. Okay.
Okay.</i>

565
00:46:16,985 --> 00:46:19,988
- There we are.
- Thank you. Thank you, Doctor.

566
00:46:20,072 --> 00:46:24,243
<i>- I thought I was losing him.
- It's okay. He's gonna be fine.</i>

567
00:46:27,162 --> 00:46:30,457
<i>Could you, uh- Could you move the toys
from that bed, please?</i>

568
00:46:30,582 --> 00:46:32,709
Could you move the toys
from that bed, please?

569
00:46:38,674 --> 00:46:42,427
Ah.

570
00:46:42,553 --> 00:46:46,014
Big boy.
Big boy.

571
00:46:46,098 --> 00:46:48,100
Here we go.

572
00:46:50,435 --> 00:46:53,146
It's okay, baby.
I'm so sorry.

573
00:46:53,272 --> 00:46:55,482
It's okay.
Don't say sorry.

574
00:46:55,607 --> 00:46:57,860
<i>Don't say sorry.</i>

575
00:46:57,943 --> 00:47:01,154
- This is where you live?
- Yes.

576
00:47:01,280 --> 00:47:03,240
Why not at State House
with the other wives?

577
00:47:03,365 --> 00:47:07,369
Since I had Mackenzie, my husband prefers us
to be somewhere more private.

578
00:47:07,452 --> 00:47:09,329
That's ridiculous.

579
00:47:11,123 --> 00:47:13,125
<i>I think this child
has epilepsy.</i>

580
00:47:13,208 --> 00:47:15,169
It's a perfectly treatable
condition.

581
00:47:17,296 --> 00:47:21,550
- The president does visit you here?
- He visits the children, not me.

582
00:47:23,552 --> 00:47:26,180
I am a bad omen.

583
00:47:29,725 --> 00:47:31,435
Okay.

584
00:47:31,518 --> 00:47:34,229
Okay, I'm gonna make an appointment
for Mackenzie at the hospital.

585
00:47:34,313 --> 00:47:36,732
All right?

586
00:47:36,815 --> 00:47:39,318
I will tell the president
how helpful you have been.

587
00:48:49,096 --> 00:48:50,806
<i>Very nice.</i>

588
00:49:00,858 --> 00:49:02,734
<i>Good morning, Nicholas.</i>

589
00:49:02,860 --> 00:49:06,238
I could not go without thanking you
for helping my son-

590
00:49:06,321 --> 00:49:07,948
Don't mention it.

591
00:49:08,073 --> 00:49:10,200
and to bring you
a small gift.

592
00:49:13,328 --> 00:49:16,748
No doctor should be
without his ambulance.

593
00:49:16,874 --> 00:49:19,042
For me?

594
00:49:19,168 --> 00:49:21,587
Yes. Come. Come.
This is yours here.

595
00:49:21,712 --> 00:49:23,672
Oh.

596
00:49:24,882 --> 00:49:27,050
<i>Uh-huh?
What do you think?</i>

597
00:49:27,176 --> 00:49:29,845
Are you serious?
It-It's a fantastic gift.

598
00:49:29,928 --> 00:49:32,556
Are you happy now? Eh?
Let's try it.

599
00:49:32,639 --> 00:49:35,767
You can drive me to the airport.
I have to fly to Libya on business.

600
00:49:35,893 --> 00:49:39,605
- Don't you think that I should get dressed?
- Quickly then. Quickly.

601
00:49:39,730 --> 00:49:41,899
- Now? Right.
- Yes.

602
00:49:41,982 --> 00:49:43,942
I'll just be a minute.

603
00:49:50,949 --> 00:49:54,494
- Are you comfortable here?
- Yeah, very much. Thank you.

604
00:49:54,620 --> 00:49:56,496
Ah.

605
00:50:03,712 --> 00:50:07,883
So, uh, it- it was Obote's men
who attacked the prison, yeah?

606
00:50:07,966 --> 00:50:09,968
- Yes.
- Right.

607
00:50:10,093 --> 00:50:14,181
We heard the gunfire
all the way at the hospital.

608
00:50:14,306 --> 00:50:18,227
- Yes, and my soldiers, they held them off.
- Oh, right.

609
00:50:18,352 --> 00:50:20,437
<i>We thought we were going
to be inundated with casualties.</i>

610
00:50:20,521 --> 00:50:23,315
Do you want to drive your car?
I want to see you drive your car.

611
00:50:23,440 --> 00:50:25,317
- Okay.
- Please. Come.

612
00:50:25,442 --> 00:50:27,319
- Come.
- Okay. Okay.

613
00:50:37,663 --> 00:50:41,583
So, you do not like the way
I treat my son.

614
00:50:43,585 --> 00:50:47,381
Uh, no.
No, I don't.

615
00:50:47,506 --> 00:50:50,676
Hiding him away like that,
it's-it's ruining his life.

616
00:50:50,801 --> 00:50:53,345
That boy
has everything he wants.

617
00:50:53,470 --> 00:50:56,056
Except the treatment
that could save him.

618
00:50:56,181 --> 00:50:58,934
He has comfort
and luxury in life.

619
00:50:59,017 --> 00:51:03,522
- Money? Sir, it's no substitute for anything.
- Nicholas.

620
00:51:03,647 --> 00:51:05,941
You have never been poor.

621
00:51:07,693 --> 00:51:09,987
What about Kay?
Don't you think it's, uh-

622
00:51:10,070 --> 00:51:13,156
Do not speak about things
you do not understand.

623
00:51:17,703 --> 00:51:20,080
But the way
you are concerned...

624
00:51:20,205 --> 00:51:23,542
it has touched me,
and I will consider.

625
00:51:24,793 --> 00:51:29,256
You know, I like this type
of frank conversation.

626
00:51:29,381 --> 00:51:32,342
Yes. I respect
your honesty...

627
00:51:32,467 --> 00:51:34,344
<i>and your opinion
completely.</i>

628
00:51:35,888 --> 00:51:38,098
- Nicholas!
- Stop!

629
00:51:42,853 --> 00:51:44,855
- Shit! Shit!
- Drive! Drive.

630
00:51:50,319 --> 00:51:53,363
<i>Drive past! Drive!</i>

631
00:51:55,991 --> 00:51:58,911
Drive!

632
00:52:16,553 --> 00:52:19,306
Obote's men!
I'm sure of it!

633
00:52:19,431 --> 00:52:21,892
If I had not been
in your car-

634
00:52:22,017 --> 00:52:26,271
But... it is in my dream.

635
00:52:26,396 --> 00:52:30,108
They cannot kill me. It is in my dream.

636
00:52:35,280 --> 00:52:38,992
<i>Somebody told his men
my travel plans.</i>

637
00:52:40,452 --> 00:52:42,913
Somebody is betraying me.

638
00:52:43,914 --> 00:52:46,667
<i>I cannot trust... anybody.</i>

639
00:52:47,876 --> 00:52:50,379
I'm surrounded...
by traitors!

640
00:52:58,512 --> 00:53:01,849
Masanga.

641
00:53:01,974 --> 00:53:04,977
Nicholas.
Nicholas.

642
00:53:05,102 --> 00:53:09,815
<i>You know Masanga?
He is one of my people.</i>

643
00:53:09,940 --> 00:53:14,528
He will handle all
of my security matters from now on.

644
00:53:14,653 --> 00:53:16,446
Yes, sir.

645
00:53:16,572 --> 00:53:21,326
- You will take care of me and this country.
- Yes, sir.

646
00:53:23,745 --> 00:53:26,874
Where is Jonah Wasswa?
Where is he?

647
00:53:26,999 --> 00:53:29,835
I need my minister.

648
00:53:29,960 --> 00:53:34,965
A minister should be
by his president's side.

649
00:53:35,048 --> 00:53:37,718
- Where is he?
- I don't know.

650
00:53:37,843 --> 00:53:42,723
And you call yourself
my closest advisor?

651
00:53:45,809 --> 00:53:49,062
Huh?

652
00:53:54,109 --> 00:53:56,528
You see?

653
00:53:56,653 --> 00:53:59,072
You see?
These loyal soldiers...

654
00:53:59,198 --> 00:54:01,575
already they have
captured the criminals.

655
00:54:26,058 --> 00:54:30,687
Do not pity them,
Nicholas.

656
00:54:30,771 --> 00:54:34,107
These men here,
they wanted you dead.

657
00:54:36,527 --> 00:54:38,862
Why did you try to kill me?

658
00:54:40,697 --> 00:54:42,574
<i>Huh?</i>

659
00:54:43,617 --> 00:54:47,704
<i>I will not die...
until I say!</i>

660
00:54:50,582 --> 00:54:54,378
Look at me!

661
00:54:58,257 --> 00:55:01,718
<i>Obote!</i>

662
00:55:01,844 --> 00:55:03,929
Huh?

663
00:55:04,054 --> 00:55:06,056
<i>You work for him!</i>

664
00:55:06,139 --> 00:55:08,600
Obote! Huh?

665
00:55:08,725 --> 00:55:12,938
That-That...
drunk, silly man!

666
00:55:13,063 --> 00:55:17,442
You want to kill me
for that drunk, silly man?

667
00:55:17,568 --> 00:55:19,444
Huh?

668
00:55:24,575 --> 00:55:26,535
Uganda loves me...

669
00:55:28,370 --> 00:55:32,165
because I am loyal...

670
00:55:32,291 --> 00:55:34,585
and I am fair.

671
00:55:38,463 --> 00:55:41,758
I am your president.

672
00:55:50,893 --> 00:55:52,895
Come, Nicholas.

673
00:55:52,978 --> 00:55:53,645
<i>This is no place for us.</i>

674
00:57:43,463 --> 00:57:45,883
<i>These I can read you later.</i>

675
00:57:46,008 --> 00:57:48,927
And the rest-The rest
are just pro forma papers for you to sign.

676
00:57:49,052 --> 00:57:52,222
Um, I left a small list
of medical equipment at the end...

677
00:57:52,347 --> 00:57:54,808
<i>for my old surgery
in Mgambo.</i>

678
00:58:05,485 --> 00:58:07,696
<i>Is there anything else,
Nicholas?</i>

679
00:58:14,494 --> 00:58:16,455
Eh?

680
00:58:18,874 --> 00:58:21,126
Nicholas?

681
00:58:21,210 --> 00:58:23,337
It's probably nothing, sir.

682
00:58:28,133 --> 00:58:30,093
What?

683
00:58:33,680 --> 00:58:39,186
Nicholas, you are
my closest advisor.

684
00:58:39,561 --> 00:58:42,105
<i>Please.</i>

685
00:58:42,189 --> 00:58:44,149
<i>Tell me
what is on your mind.</i>

686
00:58:51,406 --> 00:58:54,451
Last night, I went to the Holiday Inn
and had a drink.

687
00:58:56,954 --> 00:59:00,999
I saw Jonah Wasswa there
speaking to some white guy in the bar.

688
00:59:02,167 --> 00:59:06,088
<i>Something about it
just didn't seem right.</i>

689
00:59:06,213 --> 00:59:08,799
It's- It's probably nothing...

690
00:59:08,924 --> 00:59:11,510
but, uh, you might wanna
have a talk with him.

691
00:59:11,635 --> 00:59:13,595
Just- Just a talk.

692
00:59:16,974 --> 00:59:18,934
<i>Like I say,

693
00:59:26,275 --> 00:59:28,235
Good night, sir.

694
00:59:51,758 --> 00:59:55,596
- Ah. How are you?
- Very well. How are you?

695
00:59:55,721 --> 00:59:58,015
Very well.
See you next week.

696
00:59:58,140 --> 01:00:01,351
Would you care for a drink?

697
01:00:02,686 --> 01:00:06,648
That's very good, Mackenzie.

698
01:00:11,695 --> 01:00:13,614
<i>Very good.
Go show your brother.</i>

699
01:00:20,204 --> 01:00:22,122
<i>Hiya.</i>

700
01:00:24,875 --> 01:00:26,919
Hiya.

701
01:00:29,379 --> 01:00:32,508
Uh, he's looking
much better.

702
01:00:32,591 --> 01:00:35,552
Much better.

703
01:00:35,636 --> 01:00:37,888
That other one is Campbell.

704
01:00:38,013 --> 01:00:39,973
He is the one
who got your T-shirt.

705
01:00:40,057 --> 01:00:42,351
You're a man of taste.

706
01:00:43,602 --> 01:00:46,021
<i>Mummy! Mummy!</i>

707
01:00:46,104 --> 01:00:50,108
Please, goodbye.

708
01:00:50,234 --> 01:00:52,611
<i>- Mummy! He keeps pushing me! Mummy!
- Okay, stop it.</i>

709
01:00:52,736 --> 01:00:55,906
<i>Stop it, Mackenzie.</i>

710
01:00:56,031 --> 01:01:00,285
<i>Dr. Garrigan. Daydreaming?</i>

711
01:01:00,410 --> 01:01:03,539
Well, looking at you, Stone,
I certainly hope so.

712
01:01:03,622 --> 01:01:06,124
I wasn't expecting to find you here.

713
01:01:06,208 --> 01:01:08,710
I thought you'd be with the president
on his trip to London.

714
01:01:08,794 --> 01:01:10,712
No, I'm needed here.

715
01:01:10,796 --> 01:01:15,008
- I do hope the man hasn't blown up again.
- Uh, what?

716
01:01:15,092 --> 01:01:19,054
<i>I was reading this article in the Times.
I don't know if you've seen it.</i>

717
01:01:19,137 --> 01:01:23,058
<i>It seems a high court judge who recently
ruled against Amin has gone missing.</i>

718
01:01:23,183 --> 01:01:27,646
<i>- Hasn't been seen for five days.
- I'm sure there's a perfectly logical explanation.</i>

719
01:01:27,729 --> 01:01:29,857
Well, the thing is,
we've been getting reports...

720
01:01:29,982 --> 01:01:32,943
up and down the country
of the same thing.

721
01:01:33,068 --> 01:01:36,363
People speaking out
against the regime...

722
01:01:36,446 --> 01:01:38,532
just, uh, disappearing.

723
01:01:38,615 --> 01:01:42,035
No. Look, if you're gonna accuse the president
of something, you just come out and say it.

724
01:01:42,119 --> 01:01:44,371
- All right?
- I was just hoping you might be able...

725
01:01:44,496 --> 01:01:46,999
to give us a little
clarification.

726
01:01:47,082 --> 01:01:50,669
Oh, fuck your clarifications,
Stone! Fuck them.

727
01:01:52,254 --> 01:01:54,256
You people amaze me.

